  "root_text": {
    "iti88:0.1": "Itivuttaka 88 ",
    "iti88:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti88:0.3": "Catutthavagga ",
    "iti88:0.4": "Antarāmalasutta ",
    "iti88:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti88:2.1": "“Tayome, bhikkhave, antarāmalā antarāamittā antarāsapattā antarāvadhakā antarāpaccatthikā. ",
    "iti88:2.2": "Katame tayo? ",
    "iti88:2.3": "Lobho, bhikkhave, antarāmalo antarāamitto antarāsapatto antarāvadhako antarāpaccatthiko. ",
    "iti88:2.4": "Doso, bhikkhave, antarāmalo antarāamitto antarāsapatto antarāvadhako antarāpaccatthiko. ",
    "iti88:2.5": "Moho, bhikkhave, antarāmalo antarāamitto antarāsapatto antarāvadhako antarāpaccatthiko. ",
    "iti88:2.6": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo antarāmalā antarāamittā antarāsapattā antarāvadhakā antarāpaccatthikā”ti. ",
    "iti88:2.7": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti88:2.8": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti88:3.1": "“Anatthajanano lobho, ",
    "iti88:3.2": "lobho cittappakopano; ",
    "iti88:3.3": "Bhayamantarato jātaṁ, ",
    "iti88:3.4": "taṁ jano nāvabujjhati. ",
    "iti88:4.1": "Luddho atthaṁ na jānāti, ",
    "iti88:4.2": "luddho dhammaṁ na passati; ",
    "iti88:4.3": "Andhatamaṁ tadā hoti, ",
    "iti88:4.4": "yaṁ lobho sahate naraṁ. ",
    "iti88:5.1": "Yo ca lobhaṁ pahantvāna, ",
    "iti88:5.2": "lobhaneyye na lubbhati; ",
    "iti88:5.3": "Lobho pahīyate tamhā, ",
    "iti88:5.4": "udabindūva pokkharā. ",
    "iti88:6.1": "Anatthajanano doso, ",
    "iti88:6.2": "doso cittappakopano; ",
    "iti88:6.3": "Bhayamantarato jātaṁ, ",
    "iti88:6.4": "taṁ jano nāvabujjhati. ",
    "iti88:7.1": "Duṭṭho atthaṁ na jānāti, ",
    "iti88:7.2": "duṭṭho dhammaṁ na passati; ",
    "iti88:7.3": "Andhatamaṁ tadā hoti, ",
    "iti88:7.4": "yaṁ doso sahate naraṁ. ",
    "iti88:8.1": "Yo ca dosaṁ pahantvāna, ",
    "iti88:8.2": "dosaneyye na dussati; ",
    "iti88:8.3": "Doso pahīyate tamhā, ",
    "iti88:8.4": "tālapakkaṁva bandhanā. ",
    "iti88:9.1": "Anatthajanano moho, ",
    "iti88:9.2": "moho cittappakopano; ",
    "iti88:9.3": "Bhayamantarato jātaṁ, ",
    "iti88:9.4": "taṁ jano nāvabujjhati. ",
    "iti88:10.1": "Mūḷho atthaṁ na jānāti, ",
    "iti88:10.2": "mūḷho dhammaṁ na passati; ",
    "iti88:10.3": "Andhatamaṁ tadā hoti, ",
    "iti88:10.4": "yaṁ moho sahate naraṁ. ",
    "iti88:11.1": "Yo ca mohaṁ pahantvāna, ",
    "iti88:11.2": "mohaneyye na muyhati; ",
    "iti88:11.3": "Mohaṁ vihanti so sabbaṁ, ",
    "iti88:11.4": "ādiccovudayaṁ taman”ti. ",
    "iti88:12.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti88:12.2": "Navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti88:0.1": "So It Was Said 88 ",
    "iti88:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti88:0.3": "Chapter Four ",
    "iti88:0.4": "Inner Stains ",
    "iti88:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti88:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three inner stains, inner foes, inner enemies, inner killers, and inner adversaries. ",
    "iti88:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti88:2.3": "Greed, ",
    "iti88:2.4": "hate, ",
    "iti88:2.5": "and delusion. ",
    "iti88:2.6": "These three are inner stains, inner foes, inner enemies, inner killers, and inner adversaries.” ",
    "iti88:2.7": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti88:2.8": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti88:3.1": "“Greed creates harm; ",
    "iti88:3.2": "greed upsets the mind. ",
    "iti88:3.3": "That person doesn’t recognize ",
    "iti88:3.4": "the danger that arises within. ",
    "iti88:4.1": "A greedy person doesn’t know the good. ",
    "iti88:4.2": "A greedy person doesn’t see the truth. ",
    "iti88:4.3": "When a person is beset by greed, ",
    "iti88:4.4": "only blind darkness is left. ",
    "iti88:5.1": "Those who have given up greed, ",
    "iti88:5.2": "don’t get greedy even when provoked. ",
    "iti88:5.3": "Greed falls off them ",
    "iti88:5.4": "like a drop from a lotus-leaf. ",
    "iti88:6.1": "Hate creates harm; ",
    "iti88:6.2": "hate upsets the mind. ",
    "iti88:6.3": "That person doesn’t recognize ",
    "iti88:6.4": "the danger that arises within. ",
    "iti88:7.1": "A hateful person doesn’t know the good. ",
    "iti88:7.2": "A hateful person doesn’t see the truth. ",
    "iti88:7.3": "When a person is beset by hate, ",
    "iti88:7.4": "only blind darkness is left. ",
    "iti88:8.1": "Those who have given up hate, ",
    "iti88:8.2": "don’t get angry even when provoked. ",
    "iti88:8.3": "Hate falls off them ",
    "iti88:8.4": "like a palm-leaf from its stem. ",
    "iti88:9.1": "Delusion creates harm; ",
    "iti88:9.2": "delusion upsets the mind. ",
    "iti88:9.3": "That person doesn’t recognize ",
    "iti88:9.4": "the danger that arises within. ",
    "iti88:10.1": "A deluded person doesn’t know the good. ",
    "iti88:10.2": "A deluded person doesn’t see the truth. ",
    "iti88:10.3": "When a person is beset by delusion, ",
    "iti88:10.4": "only blind darkness is left. ",
    "iti88:11.1": "Those who have given up delusion, ",
    "iti88:11.2": "don’t get deluded even when provoked. ",
    "iti88:11.3": "They banish all delusion, ",
    "iti88:11.4": "as the rising sun the dark.” ",
    "iti88:12.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
